   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNDP/Sudan CHF, 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The humanitarian situation in Sudan is still extremely critical. Around 6.1 million people are in need of humanitarian assistance. More than half of these people are located in Darfur. Approximately 600.000 refugees from Sudan are located in the neighbouring countries Chad, Ethiopia and South Sudan. The UN&#xBF;s total appeal for Sudan is USD 995 million, and only one percent is yet covered. In 2013 the appeal has same size and only 57 percent was covered. 
In 2013 Denmark contributed with DKK 20 million to emergent efforts on South Sudan, and over the past two years Denmark has contributed to the UN&apos;s humanitarian country fund for Sudan with DKK 20 million yearly.</narrative>
  </description>
